#. Tag: para
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "OpenOffice.org contributors have set up a foundation (<emphasis>The Document Foundation</emphasis>) to foster project development. The idea had been discussed for some time, but the actual trigger was Oracle's acquisition of Sun. The new ownership made the future of OpenOffice under Oracle uncertain. Since Oracle declined to join the foundation, the developers had to give up on the OpenOffice.org name. The software is now known as <emphasis>Libre Office</emphasis>."
